"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-team-gb-climbing-cycling-medals-day-15-paris-olympics-3220222\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  We are officially into the final weekend of theParis Olympicsas the clock ticks down to Sunday's closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GBhave already surpassed their minimum medal target of 55 going into the last throes of competition, but there could be plenty more on the way.\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"British athletes are hoping to be in contention in the 4x400m in both the men's and women's category after Noah Williams won bronze in the men's 10m platform diving final.\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 312, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8648519365573657, \"rank\": 0.1550829529732473, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 419, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"score\": 0.999998273608197, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Georgia Bell also beat Laura Muir to 1,500m bronze in the women's final, running a national record time, before GB's runners added a third and fourth bronze in the men's and women's 4x400m relay.\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 485, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.936680095034518, \"rank\": 0.04638076789825796, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}, {\"begin\": 508, \"end\": 518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Muir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Muir\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Muir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Muir\"}, {\"begin\": 597, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9958380071619608, \"rank\": 0.004179383834645407, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in the pool, Kate Shortman and Isabelle Thorpe earned Team GB's first ever artistic swimming medal, finishing with a shock silver.\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Shortman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\"}, {\"begin\": 717, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Isabelle Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999706857137693, \"rank\": 2.9315144012758353e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This live blog is now closed.\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well that's it from the final Saturday of Paris 2024, and what a day it's been.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Six medals for Team GB - four bronzes and two silvers, including that historic first artistic silver prize.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999706857137693, \"rank\": 2.9315144012758353e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We will be back for the final day of these Games tomorrow with all the action from the cycling, modern pentathlon and closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver for 21-year-old Caden Cunningham.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999977839072016, \"rank\": 2.216095552963206e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Salimi showed his greater experience to ease to gold in the end.\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, it's the 63rd medal for Team GB - hitting the pre-Games target.\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Salimi, the taller man, storms back to win the second round 9-1.\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Got to be favourite now.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cunningham needs some big energy in the third and final round.\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999977839072016, \"rank\": 2.216095552963206e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First round to Cunningham.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1524, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999977839072016, \"rank\": 2.216095552963206e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mind you, Rebecca McGowan won the opener in her bronze medal match and lost out in a tight third.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\", \"score\": 0.9999947512179875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca McGowan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us\\u00a0see him shut it out in two for gold.\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Caden Cunningham under way against Arian Salimi in the taekwondo 80kg final.\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999977839072016, \"rank\": 2.216095552963206e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lands the first scoring point, concedes one to the head, and lands again to the body.\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quick start from both fighters.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Caden Cunningham is nearly 25 minutes late in starting his +80kg gold medal match, but the Terminator emerges at the Grand Palais.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 2007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1883, \"end\": 1893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999977839072016, \"rank\": 2.216095552963206e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}, {\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.054434697357538e-32, \"text\": \"gold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will face Iran's Arian Salimi for Team GB's first ever men's taekwondo gold.\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2022, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999952078879913, \"rank\": 4.7921152464465675e-06, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rebecca McGowan is beaten at the death and Nafia Kus takes bronze.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2090, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\", \"score\": 0.9999947512179875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca McGowan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\"}, {\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\", \"score\": 0.9999998071707709, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Disappointing for the Brit but she will be back.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2205, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One thing Paris have really messed up is the medal ceremonies at the athletics.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.477465204470798e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before or in this case after every session, there are four or five medal ceremonies one after another, which I think really lose some of their specialness when there rare, as there are tonight, eight in a row over the course of an hour with nothing else going on.\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stadium will be mostly empty by the time the 4x400m relay runners come through to pick up their bronzes.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nafia Kus wins the second round 4-2.\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2668, \"end\": 2671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\", \"score\": 0.9999998071707709, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rebecca McGowan will have to win a decider if she wants Olympic bronze.\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2699, \"end\": 2714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_McGowan\", \"score\": 0.9999947512179875, \"rank\": 0.0, \