//dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 3027, \"end\": 3033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9997949401296369, \"rank\": 0.00020510183940241207, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3042, \"end\": 3045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\", \"score\": 0.9999998071707709, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kus\"}, {\"begin\": 3046, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aidin_Vilayet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2650964273420698e-18, \"text\": \"Aydin\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aidin_Vilayet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aidin_Vilayet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had to come through the repechage to get here after being initially knocked out in the quarter finals, but her +67kg fight is about to begin at the Grand Palais.\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This reaction \\ud83e\\udd79Kate Shortman and Isabelle Thorpe are guaranteed a medal in the  women's duet!The first-ever for@TeamGBin artistic swimming.#BBCOlympics#Paris2024#Olympicspic.twitter.com/aRkJj2cHGq  Another bronze for the Brits in the 4x400m, Amber Anning just overhauled in the final few metres by who else but Femke Bol.\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3263, \"end\": 3276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Shortman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\"}, {\"begin\": 3281, \"end\": 3296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Isabelle Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\"}, {\"begin\": 3559, \"end\": 3568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course the Americans won it, and came within a tenth of a second of breaking a world record that has stood for 36 years.\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's 4x400m relay is under way.\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hard to understate how significant that is.\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kate Shortman and Isabelle Thorpe have won silver for Team GB in the artistic swimming, the nation's first ever.\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3780, \"end\": 3793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Shortman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Shortman\"}, {\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Isabelle Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabelle_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What an achievement.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They produced the highest score in the free routine section of the final.\", \"from\": 3914, \"to\": 3987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stunning.\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 3997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A high jump champion at last!\", \"from\": 3999, \"to\": 4028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it's Hamish Kerr of New Zealand who sprints into the middle of the field in celebration.\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4039, \"end\": 4050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"score\": 0.9999998928324261, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamish Kerr\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\"}, {\"begin\": 4054, \"end\": 4065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.998759182623992, \"rank\": 0.0008362254574430543, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Good thing the javelin has finished\\u2026  Oh what a race!\", \"from\": 4123, \"to\": 4176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA and Botswana ago toe-to-toe the whole way down and the Americans win it by a tenth of a second.\", \"from\": 4177, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Charlie Dobson was never going to be able to run down the two ahead of him, they had 10 metres to start with, but he secures bronze for Great Britain and the team have broken the European record too, running 2:55.83.\", \"from\": 4278, \"to\": 4494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4287, \"end\": 4293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"score\": 0.9999999867309272, \"rank\": 1.3002629128994952e-08, \"text\": \"Dobson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\"}, {\"begin\": 4415, \"end\": 4428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9892339874875298, \"rank\": 0.0108831780593905, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4458, \"end\": 4473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.223469154404347e-18, \"text\": \"European record\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gasps in the stadium though as France were shoved off the track in the final lap, tangling with Belgium and South Africa.\", \"from\": 4496, \"to\": 4617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4528, \"end\": 4534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9987304613139141, \"rank\": 0.0012670926971761459, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4593, \"end\": 4600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.7546098826032107, \"rank\": 0.3247118239944996, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 4605, \"end\": 4617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.7897682936488085, \"rank\": 0.2649342763898621, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well they have both failed at 2.36m and the bar is going down to 2.34m for gold, which is the same height Sottile in fourth cleared, bizarrely.\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All a bit weird but we have the 4x400m relay first anyway, so they will wait for that to finish.\", \"from\": 4764, \"to\": 4860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortman and Thorpe perform their \\\"Rising Phoenix\\\" routine, apparently representing the rebirth of artistic swimming.\", \"from\": 4862, \"to\": 4979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4876, \"end\": 4882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"score\": 0.9993685418854519, \"rank\": 0.000587883443161911, \"text\": \"Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They look pretty synchronised to me.\", \"from\": 4981, \"to\": 5017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are guaranteed a medal - they get 294.5085 for their routine, the highest of the day so far.\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two pairings to go.\", \"from\": 5117, \"to\": 5136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where will the British pair finish?\", \"from\": 5137, \"to\": 5172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5153, \"end\": 5160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8648519365573657, \"rank\": 0.1550829529732473, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are pioneers regardless.\", \"from\": 5173, \"to\": 5202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Erm, there is some confusion in the high jump.\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The monitors had been showing Hamish Kerr as the leader on his own, on countback, and that has now been revised for him to be tied for first with Shelby McEwen.\", \"from\": 5251, \"to\": 5411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5282, \"end\": 5293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"score\": 0.9999998928324261, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamish Kerr\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\"}, {\"begin\": 5398, \"end\": 5411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\", \"score\": 0.9999970370593713, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelby McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have both failed three times at 2.38m - but there is no shared gold this time: instead, it is a jump-off for gold.\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The bar stays at 2.38m and it is basically sudden death now.\", \"from\": 5533, \"to\": 5593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Curious.\", \"from\": 5595, \"to\": 5603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 5605, \"to\": 5662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 5663, \"to\": 5700, \"entities\": []}]}"